{"entries":[{"id":"classic-walter-de-maria","name":"Walter De Maria","category":"藝術家","tier":"經典檔案庫","region":"西方","country":"美國","media":["地景/大地藝術","雕塑"],"works":"The Lightning Field；The New York Earth Room；The Broken Kilometer","comment":"以極少形式承接巨大自然能量；The Lightning Field 是等待、距離與天候共同完成的作品。","website":"https://www.diaart.org/artist/walter-de-maria","workPage":"https://www.diaart.org/visit/visit-our-locations-sites/walter-de-maria-the-lightning-field","photo":"https://www.diaart.org/artist/walter-de-maria","classicTitle":"The Lightning Field","classicImage":"https://media.newyorker.com/photos/590968cd019dfc3494ea1089/16:9/w_1280,c_limit/110418_r20759_g2048.jpg","classicDesc":"The Lightning Field 在新墨西哥高原排列 400 支不鏽鋼柱，等待光、天候與閃電改變場域。作品要求停留與等待，讓公共藝術從觀看物件轉向經歷時間。","status":"可信二手來源","updated":"2026-07-03"},{"id":"classic-nancy-holt","name":"Nancy Holt","category":"藝術家","tier":"經典檔案庫","region":"西方","country":"美國","media":["地景/大地藝術","建築/場域","光/影像/投影"],"works":"Sun Tunnels；Dark Star Park；Hydra's Head","comment":"她讓地景藝術進入時間、天文與觀看框架；作品不是佔據自然，而是校準感知。","website":"https://holtsmithsonfoundation.org/nancy-holt","workPage":"https://holtsmithsonfoundation.org/sun-tunnels","photo":"https://holtsmithsonfoundation.org/nancy-holt","classicTitle":"Sun Tunnels","classicImage":"https://holtsmithsonfoundation.org/sites/default/files/styles/fullscreen_2048_x_y_/public/2020-02/Holt-SunTunnels-DawnDusk-030-2048pxW.jpg?itok=BuIbYX1k","classicDesc":"Sun Tunnels 由四支混凝土管在猶他沙漠中對準冬夏至日出日落。它把雕塑變成天文儀器與觀看框架，讓觀眾意識到時間、光線與自身位置。","status":"官方來源","updated":"2026-07-03"},{"id":"classic-mary-miss","name":"Mary Miss","category":"藝術家","tier":"經典檔案庫","region":"西方","country":"美國","media":["建築/場域","地景/大地藝術","社會參與"],"works":"Perimeters/Pavilions/Decoys；City as Living Laboratory","comment":"她把公共藝術轉向城市閱讀、環境教育與參與式場域；是被低估但非常關鍵的一脈。","website":"https://www.marymiss.com/","workPage":"https://www.marymiss.com/","photo":"https://www.marymiss.com/","classicTitle":"Perimeters/Pavilions/Decoys","classicImage":"https://marymiss.com/wp-content/uploads/1977/08/MM_PPD_1978_019.jpg","classicDesc":"這件作品以木構、地下空間與觀看點引導觀眾重新讀取場地。Mary Miss 的關鍵不是製造地標，而是讓觀眾意識到自己如何在城市與地景中移動、觀察與判斷。","status":"官方來源","updated":"2026-07-03"},{"id":"classic-siah-armajani","name":"Siah Armajani","category":"藝術家","tier":"經典檔案庫","region":"西方","country":"伊朗 / 美國","media":["建築/場域","社會參與","雕塑"],"works":"Bridge works；Reading Rooms；Lighthouse and Bridge","comment":"他把橋、亭、閱讀室變成民主空間的形式語言；公共藝術在他這裡接近市民倫理。","website":"https://walkerart.org/collections/artists/siah-armajani","workPage":"https://walkerart.org/collections/artists/siah-armajani","photo":"https://walkerart.org/collections/artists/siah-armajani","classicTitle":"Bridge works","classicImage":"https://assets.walkerart.org/uploads/2025/09/Armajani-scaled.jpg?resize=1900%2C1000&gravity","classicDesc":"Armajani 的橋系列把橋視為民主隱喻：連接、通行、停留與公共使用。它們介於建築與雕塑之間，拒絕封閉藝術物件，轉而提出市民共享空間的形式問題。","status":"可信二手來源","updated":"2026-07-03"}]}